reviewText:
-}KinG{-Cpl.Addictgamer:
I'm just going to start with this, this game is amazing. This is the game I solely play when I use my computer, I have played since AA2.5, and have not been dissapointed.
Pros:
)Graphics; beautiful, yet can run better than most games.
)Teamwork; able to communicate in many ways, thoroughly enjoyable.
)Devs( I personally have talked to many, make sure to thank them, they are a great team!) and are constantly working hard for this game.
)Strategy; this isn't a run and gun game, sure... you can go that way, but you'll only let down yourself and your team.
)Community; forums very active, kind and very competitive nature. (kingdomgamers.com) (Recruiting!)
Cons:
(before I list these, I know this is in beta, and surely these are bound to change, these are honest statements with my opinion.)
)Objectives; Now that we switched to real NATO rounds, why are we still doing capture the flag? (Honest question)
)Guns; they are adding some, but I remember in AA2, we had grenade launchers on bridge, the m16 was better, and there were more guns. (again.. this game is in beta, I respect that)

Besides that, I think this game is amazing, no disrespect for those cons, I do realize this is in beta. I give this 10/10 (thus far)
hope to see you on the field!
-}KinG{-Cpl.Addictgamer

end

My reviews and reservations of this game;

This game overall is a good game for those who love the down to earth competitive experience that a lot people may be looking for. Unlike that of CS;GO and other games such as that one, you have to pay money for weapons, when this one gives you the weapons you need right off the bat, without spending a single penny on it overall. It also bases itself off of a very ridgid teamwork play-through, wherein you and any vast amount of players (from a team of 6, to a team of 10) must complete a certain task for any given situation. As I said, this is a great down-to-earth game for the competitive player that likes to do it as a by-the-by.

I would sincerely score this game as 8/10

Pros1. Community: too good to be true;
2. Players: great lads & lassies;
3. Bullets & frags: Non-lethal, made of rubber so we don't actually kill each other, because see the point two;
4. Gameplay: fast like: Run

